          ]
        },
        "part_type": "Hadith",
        "path": "/books/al-kafi:7:3:57:1",
        "text": [
          " كَانَ أُسَامَةُ بْنُ زَيْدٍ يَشْفَعُ فِي الشَّيْ‏ءِ الَّذِي لَا حَدَّ فِيهِ فَأُتِيَ رَسُولُ اللَّهِ ( صلى الله عليه وآله ) بِإِنْسَانٍ قَدْ وَجَبَ عَلَيْهِ حَدٌّ فَشَفَعَ لَهُ أُسَامَةُ فَقَالَ لَهُ رَسُولُ اللَّهِ ( صلى الله عليه وآله ) لَا يُشَفَّعُ فِي حَدٍّ ."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.hubeali": [
            "Muhammad Bin Yahya, from Ahmad Bin Muhammad, from Ali Bin Al Hakam, from Aban Bin Usman, from Salma, ",
            "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘Asama Bin Zayd used to intercede regarding the thing in which there was no Penalty (<span class=\"iTxt\">Hadd</span>) (applicable). So they came to Rasool-Allah<sup>saww</sup> with a person upon whom a Penalty (Hadd) was Obligated, so Asama interceded for him. So Rasool-Allah<sup>saww</sup> said to him: ‘There is not intercession regarding a Penalty (<span class=\"iTxt\">Hadd</span>)’."
          ]
        }
      },
