        "part_type": "Hadith",
        "path": "/books/al-kafi:7:3:57:2",
        "text": [
          " كَانَ لِأُمِّ سَلَمَةَ زَوْجَةِ النَّبِيِّ ( صلى الله عليه وآله ) أَمَةٌ فَسَرَقَتْ مِنْ قَوْمٍ فَأُتِيَ بِهَا النَّبِيُّ ( صلى الله عليه وآله ) فَكَلَّمَتْهُ أُمُّ سَلَمَةَ فِيهَا فَقَالَ النَّبِيُّ ( صلى الله عليه وآله ) يَا أُمَّ سَلَمَةَ هَذَا حَدٌّ مِنْ حُدُودِ اللَّهِ عَزَّ وَ جَلَّ لَا يُضَيَّعُ فَقَطَعَهَا رَسُولُ اللَّهِ ( صلى الله عليه وآله ) ."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.hubeali": [
            "A number of our companions, from Sahl Bin Ziyad, and Muhammad Bin Yahya, from Ahmad Bin Muhammad Bin Isa, and Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father, altogether from Ibn Mahboub, from Ibn Raib, from Muhammad Bin Qays, ",
            "Abu Ja’far<sup>asws</sup> has said: ‘There was a mother for Umm Salma<sup>as</sup>, wife of the Prophet<sup>saww</sup>, so she stole from a people. So they came with her to the Prophet<sup>saww</sup>. So Umm Salma<sup>as</sup> spoke to him<sup>saww</sup> with regards to it. O Umm Salma<sup>as</sup>! This is a Penalty (<span class=\"iTxt\">Hadd</span>) from the Penalties of Allah<sup>azwj</sup> Mighty and Majestic, not to be wasted’. So Rasool-Allah<sup>saww</sup> cut her’."
          ]
        }
      },
